---
title: "Blog Post Template"
description: "A complete blog post template example"
layout: "base.liquid"
---

<article class="blog-post">
  <header>
    <h1>{{ post.title }}</h1>
    <div class="meta">
      <time datetime="{{ post.date | date: '%Y-%m-%d' }}">
        {{ post.date | date: '%B %d, %Y' }}
      </time>
      <span class="author">by {{ post.author.name }}</span>
      {% if post.tags.size > 0 %}
        <div class="tags">
          {% for tag in post.tags %}
            <span class="tag">{{ tag }}</span>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      {% endif %}
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="content">
    {{ post.content }}
  </div>

  {% if post.excerpt %}
    <div class="excerpt">
      <h3>Summary</h3>
      <p>{{ post.excerpt | strip_html | truncate: 200 }}</p>
    </div>
  {% endif %}

  <footer>
    <div class="reading-time">
      {{ post.content | reading_time }} min read
    </div>
    
    {% if post.related_posts.size > 0 %}
      <section class="related-posts">
        <h3>Related Posts</h3>
        {% for related in post.related_posts limit: 3 %}
          <a href="{{ related.url }}">{{ related.title }}</a>
        {% endfor %}
      </section>
    {% endif %}

    <div class="share">
      <h4>Share this post:</h4>
      <a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text={{ post.title | url_encode }}&url={{ post.url | absolute_url | url_encode }}">
        Twitter
      </a>
      <a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u={{ post.url | absolute_url | url_encode }}">
        Facebook
      </a>
    </div>
  </footer>
</article>

{% comment %}
This template demonstrates:
- Variable output with filters
- Conditional content
- Loops with limits
- Date formatting
- URL encoding
- Template inheritance (layout)
- HTML generation with Liquid
{% endcomment %}